{"id":392,"date":"2025-06-17T10:08:12","date_gmt":"2025-06-17T15:08:12","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/garageup.com\/?p=392"},"modified":"2025-06-17T13:29:29","modified_gmt":"2025-06-17T18:29:29","slug":"epoxy-flooring-2025","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/garageup.com\/blog\/2025\/06\/17\/epoxy-flooring-2025\/","title":{"rendered":"Epoxy Flooring: 2025 Guide to Stunning, Durable Floors for Homes &amp; Businesses"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Did you know that well-installed epoxy flooring can last up to 20 years with minimal upkeep? That&#8217;s two decades of shine, strength, and style\u2014without the hassle of constant repairs. Here in Austin, where the weather swings from dry and dusty to humid and stormy, having a floor that can take the heat (and the occasional flood) is more than a luxury. It&#8217;s a must.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether you\u2019re updating your garage, upgrading a retail space, or planning your dream home build, epoxy flooring is a top-tier choice. At Garage Up Austin, we specialize in garage door services\u2014but we\u2019re also big believers in giving our customers the know-how to make smart choices about every corner of their garage, including the floor. So let\u2019s dive in!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is Epoxy Flooring?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Epoxy flooring is a type of surface coating made by mixing resin and hardeners to create a tough, plastic-like material. It\u2019s poured over concrete, where it bonds tightly and cures into a strong, seamless floor.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Stronger than paint:<\/strong> While it might look like a shiny paint job, epoxy is way tougher. It resists scratches, chemicals, and stains.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Waterproof and weatherproof:<\/strong> Perfect for Austin\u2019s unpredictable weather.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Comes in styles:<\/strong> From clean, solid-color finishes to metallic swirls and decorative flakes.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You\u2019ll find epoxy flooring in homes, hospitals, schools, showrooms, warehouses, and, yes\u2014right in your garage.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Chris-Harrison-14-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"professional garage up technicians buffing a garage floor before installing epoxy flooring\" class=\"wp-image-52\" srcset=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Chris-Harrison-14-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Chris-Harrison-14-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Chris-Harrison-14-768x432.jpg 768w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Chris-Harrison-14-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Chris-Harrison-14-2048x1152.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Why Epoxy Flooring Works Great in Austin<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Austin\u2019s heat, humidity, and dust storms make traditional flooring options like carpet or untreated concrete a risky move. Here\u2019s why epoxy thrives in our Texas climate:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Temperature-resistant:<\/strong> Epoxy doesn\u2019t soften or crack under high heat.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Moisture-resistant:<\/strong> A sealed epoxy floor won\u2019t absorb rain, mud, or accidental spills.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Low maintenance:<\/strong> Dust and dirt don\u2019t stick. Just sweep and mop.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stylish options:<\/strong> Epoxy floors can match your home&#8217;s modern aesthetic or bring bold energy to a commercial space.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Environmentally friendly:<\/strong> Many epoxy products now have low VOCs, making them safer for your family and pets.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Best Places to Use Epoxy Flooring in Austin<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You\u2019d be surprised where epoxy flooring works well. It&#8217;s not just for garages anymore!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Garage Floors<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Let\u2019s start with our specialty. Garage epoxy floors are a perfect match for homeowners in Austin:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Stand up to oil leaks and heavy tools<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Easy to clean after a DIY project<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Improve lighting with a reflective surface<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Boost home value and curb appeal<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Residential Interiors<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, people are putting epoxy inside their homes!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Kitchens and bathrooms stay cleaner and look sleeker<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Basements stay dry and mold-free<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Outdoor patios resist sun damage and look stunning year-round<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"819\" src=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-9-1024x819.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-323\" srcset=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-9-1024x819.png 1024w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-9-300x240.png 300w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-9-768x614.png 768w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-9.png 1500w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Commercial Spaces<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Businesses across Austin\u2014from salons to breweries\u2014choose epoxy for its long life and polished look:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Durable enough for heavy foot traffic<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Custom colors to match your brand<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Slip-resistant textures keep staff and customers safe<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Affects Price?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Surface condition (cracks or stains need repair)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Square footage (bigger spaces = better value)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Design complexity<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Type of epoxy (water-based, solids, or polyaspartic topcoats)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Money-Saving Tips<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Bundle with other services (like garage door upgrades\u2014wink wink!)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Choose a simpler finish in low-traffic areas<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Get quotes from multiple providers<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Choosing the Right Epoxy Coating for Your Space<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There\u2019s more to epoxy than just a glossy finish. Here are the most popular styles in Austin homes and businesses:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Flake Epoxy Floors<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Small decorative chips add texture and hide dirt<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Popular for garages and gyms<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Metallic Epoxy Floors<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Swirled pigments create a 3D, high-end look<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Great for showrooms and modern interiors<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Quartz Epoxy Systems<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Sand-like texture makes it super slip-resistant<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ideal for commercial kitchens or wet areas<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Solid Color Epoxy<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Simple and classic<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Affordable and clean-looking<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>And don\u2019t forget: Add a non-slip additive for safety\u2014especially in garages and outdoor patios!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How Epoxy Flooring is Installed (Step-by-Step)<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A high-quality epoxy job requires the right prep. Here\u2019s what goes into it:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"1\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Inspection &amp; Cleaning:<\/strong> The surface is checked for cracks, oil, or moisture.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Surface Prep:<\/strong> Grinding or shot-blasting ensures the epoxy bonds tightly.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Priming:<\/strong> A base coat soaks into the concrete.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Epoxy Application:<\/strong> Multiple coats for color and design.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Top Coat:<\/strong> Adds protection, texture, and shine.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Curing Time:<\/strong> Usually 24\u201372 hours before full use.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>While DIY kits exist, we strongly recommend hiring a pro\u2014especially for garages. A professional install ensures better adhesion, a smoother look, and longer life.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"442\" src=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Chris-Harrison-53-scaled-e1749133279969-1024x442.jpg\" alt=\"a garage up technician applying finishing touches to a newly installed epoxy floor\" class=\"wp-image-54\" srcset=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Chris-Harrison-53-scaled-e1749133279969-1024x442.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Chris-Harrison-53-scaled-e1749133279969-300x129.jpg 300w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Chris-Harrison-53-scaled-e1749133279969-768x332.jpg 768w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Chris-Harrison-53-scaled-e1749133279969-1536x663.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Chris-Harrison-53-scaled-e1749133279969-2048x884.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Finding the Best Epoxy Flooring Installers in Austin<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Looking for the right team? Here\u2019s how to spot a quality epoxy flooring contractor:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Licensed and insured<\/strong> in Texas<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Locally experienced<\/strong>\u2014Austin humidity and heat matter!<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Transparent pricing<\/strong> with no surprise fees<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Portfolio of past projects<\/strong> (ask for photos!)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Great reviews<\/strong> on Yelp, Google, and Facebook<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Avoid anyone who:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Promises a one-day job (real epoxy needs time to cure)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Doesn\u2019t prep the surface properly<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Uses only water-based or low-quality epoxy<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Need a recommendation? We\u2019ve worked with several trusted local pros we\u2019d be happy to point you toward\u2014just ask!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Maintaining Your Epoxy Floor<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You\u2019ve got your dream floor. Now keep it looking fresh!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Daily &amp; Weekly Care<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Sweep with a soft broom or dust mop<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Mop with mild soap and water<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Avoid harsh chemicals or bleach<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Seasonal Maintenance<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Reapply topcoat every 3\u20135 years<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Patch small chips or cracks early<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Avoid This!<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Dragging metal across the surface<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Using high-acid cleaners<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Leaving puddles standing for days<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Good news: most homeowners find epoxy easier to clean than tile or concrete!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"819\" src=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/GU-website-photos-68-1024x819.png\" alt=\"a new garage renovation project by garage up new orleans with new epoxy floors, slat walls, lights, and fans\" class=\"wp-image-326\" srcset=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/GU-website-photos-68-1024x819.png 1024w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/GU-website-photos-68-300x240.png 300w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/GU-website-photos-68-768x614.png 768w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/GU-website-photos-68-1536x1229.png 1536w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/GU-website-photos-68.png 1875w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Common Questions About Epoxy Flooring in Austin<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How long will it last?<\/strong> With proper care, 15\u201320 years or more. Especially indoors or in a covered garage.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Is it safe for pets and kids?<\/strong> Yes! Once cured, epoxy is non-toxic and easy to clean.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Can I use epoxy on a cracked garage floor?<\/strong> Yes\u2014but cracks need to be repaired first. A good installer will handle this.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What if my garage floods?<\/strong> Epoxy is water-resistant and won\u2019t absorb moisture. Just dry and mop.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Does it get slippery?<\/strong> It can\u2014but textured finishes and anti-slip additives solve that.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Transform Your Garage with Epoxy and Garage Up Austin<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>An epoxy floor isn\u2019t just about looks. It\u2019s about making your space stronger, cleaner, and more functional. Whether you\u2019re turning your garage into a home gym, workshop, or just want a place to park your car that doesn\u2019t look like a construction site\u2014epoxy delivers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>At <a href=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/contact-us\/\" data-type=\"link\" 